
WILL USE LINUX  KERNEL STYLE GUIDE.

Use underscores for variable names. NOT camelCase.

Declare variables of the same type on the same line.

Leave one blank line between variable declarations and the first line of code.

Define CONSTANTS for special numbers.

Use capitals and underscores for constants DEFAULT_ARRAY_SIZE

Leave one blank space between operators, and one blank space after commas.

Use braces for conditionals and loops.

If p is a pointer to a structure, you should access members by using p->member.
	Rather than (*p).member.

If p is a pointer to a structure, do not surround the -> operator with spaces.
	Uuse p->id instead of p -> id.

Don't exceed 80 characters on a line. Use linecheck command to check.

Avoid Code Duplication.
